Subject: Re: [VB] re:rear hatch hinge repair & creaks

> Gease is better, however removing the hinge pins for
> lubrication on the 
> hatch is a little dangerous given the tension on those
> torsion bars. Better to go with oil in this case.

An alternative is chain lube. It sprays on, but sets into a thick grease. Readily found at a motorcycle shop. Obviously overspray can become a real mess, so plan ahead to protect adjacent areas before spraying and wipe up excess quickly. Works great for those hard to reach door mechanisms.

Jeff
